    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-30T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-30T12:00:00-05:00" n="733"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d733">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-30T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 30—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>208. <hi rend="italic">Aide-mémoire</hi> contained in your 159, October 28,<note
                        n="8" xml:id="d733fn8">See telegram no. 344, Oct. 27, to the Ambassador in
                        France, <ref target="#pg_884">p. 884</ref>. No record of a reply by the
                        Italian Government to this <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> has been
                        found in Department files.</note> has been delivered. It is impossible under
                    existing political conditions to <pb facs="1014" n="890" xml:id="pg_890"/> make
                    contact with responsible Italian officials in order to amplify by conversations
                    the purpose of the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>. As soon as possible this
                    will be done.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
